  "title": "Workplace Safety Health Officer (Contract|Tuas)",
  "description": "<p><strong>About our client: </strong>Our client operates in the water management, environmental engineering, and infrastructure consultancy sectors in Singapore<br /></p><p><strong>About the role:</strong></p><ul><li>Conduct site safety audit inspections, monitor and drive contractors’ close out of safety violations</li><li>Identify foreseeable risks and hazards in the worksite and in relation to the work activities and work sequence and assess suitability of contractors’ risk control measures.</li><li>Review contractors’ method statement, risk assessment and safe work procedure and recommend and implement practicable measures and safe work procedures</li><li>Facilitate Investigation processes and report to WSH Manager on all incidents and recommend corrective actions to prevent recurrence</li><li>Liaise with main contractor representatives, subcontractor and relevant Authorities pertaining to safety matters</li><li>Monitor follow-up actions to ensure safety compliance and close out inspection findings and observations.</li><li>Ensure SMM implementation and compliance due to COVID-19 or any other pandemic outbreaks.</li><li>Inculcate a safe working environment and promote positive safety culture and training.</li><li>Relevant duties as and when assigned by Reporting Manager</li></ul><p><strong>About you:</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma in Engineering or Workplace Safety & Health disciplines</li><li>At least 5 years of experience as a registered Workplace Safety & Health Officer (WSHO) with MOM</li><li>Highly motivated, results-oriented and good team player</li><li>Able to manage contractors and consultants.</li><li>Good written and oral communication skills.</li><li>Able to work independently with minimum guidance and meeting tight deadlines and report effectively to the WSH Manager</li><li>Comfortable to work in construction site in the western side of Singapore</li></ul><p><strong>Other information:</strong></p><ul><li>Work location: Tuas (company transport provided)</li><li>Working days: 5.5 days</li><li>Contract duration: 1-year (renewable)</li></ul><p>*Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.*<br /></p><p>Employment Agency: Kingsforce Management Services Pte. Ltd.</p><p>Employment Agency Licence No: 94C3545</p><p>EA Personnel: Kimberly Wong</p><p>EA Personnel Reg. No.: R1984508</p>",
